==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Overview'''''</span>==

'''Level 481''' is known as '''Garschall's Cave''' after the man of the same name. The level consists of a marble cave, with calming water all around it. '''Level 481''' does not contain any natural danger, though entities within the level can cause some harm if one provokes them in any way. '''Level 481''' is mainly known for its calming waters. As such, a few groups have attempted to access the level in order to secure elements of the water for itself. While one or two have been successful, the level is difficult to access, leading to it being preserved by both a few people who want to protect the level from intruders and '''The Cave Natives''' defending off their home from any hostile elements.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Description'''''</span>===
{{Blurimage|file=Ethereal Waters.png|caption=Photo of '''Level 481'''.|align=right}}
The caves in '''Level 481''' are all made out of marble, and all of the cave surfaces are naturally smooth and will not cause unintentional harm to anyone in the level. The marble itself has unnatural properties not found in naturally found marble anywhere else. The marble in '''Level 481''' when mined, will always turn into water ten minutes after initial detachment from the caves. This water was found to be normal water with no special properties; however, when the marble water comes into contact with the calming waters, it boosts the calming water's effects to the point that even when one is not in '''The Calming Waters''', properties of the water will merge into the air for around 1-2 minutes before the effects in the air die down.

The gravity in '''Level 481''' is normal to people, but not to the waters that inhabit it. The water in the level can be both in the ground and to the ceilings of the caves. As such, if one throws an object up to the ceiling water, the resulting splash will, instead of falling to the ground, fall back up to the ceiling water. 

==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''The Calming Waters'''''</span>==

The Calming Waters is all of the water encompassed in '''Level 481'''. The water has a light-blueish hue to it and has an element of providing a natural light for the level itself. The amount of light generated by the water depends on how deep the water goes. The deeper the water goes, the more light is produced by the water.

If one steps into the calming waters, their mental state will start to gradually calm down. After 1-2 minutes in the water, all anxieties and worries will clear from one's mind, and instead one will have calming thoughts. After 25-30 minutes in the water, one will start to have more water-related calming thoughts. After an hour in the calming waters, bad memories altogether will start to be permanently going away, and after around an hour and 15-20 minutes in the water, all bad memories will be gone from their minds. It has been recommended by various wanderers that one must exit the water after this, as the effects after an hour and a half will start to harm one's self rather than help them.

After 2 hours have passed and one is still in the water, they will both start to have illusions of coloredpin fish floating through the air and the cave around them having various colors that the cave does not have. After 3 hours in the water, one will both express a desire to never leave the water at all, and their memories will be slowly altered by the water in ways that make it seem like water has always been an element in their lives they couldn't live without. Examples of their memories being altered by the calming water include that everything they have ever drank is all water, memories of always living nearby lakes or oceans even if they have never lived near natural bodies of water, etc.

After one has been in the calming waters for 5 hours, their bodies will start to fail. Despite starting to fail however, no pain seems to take effect, and they will instead continue to smile. Despite their body shutting down, they will start speaking to themselves about how grateful their life has been and will thank the water for showing them that. After around 5 minutes of body failure, their bodies will finally shut down, and the water will slowly dissolve the body into nothing.


==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Entities'''''</span>==


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''The Calming Fish'''''</span>===

The Calming Fish are a species of fish that reside in '''Level 481'''. The fish are always one of four colors: red, orange, pink and blue. The number of fish that spawn is dependent on how deep the water is. The fish will always be in packs of 2-4, and each pack will always be the same-colored fish. Each fish has a unique effect when one cooks and then tastes it. If one eats the red fish, both their hunger and thirst will be quenched for 48 hours. If one eats the pink fish, only positive memories will appear for the next hour. If one eats the orange fish, their senses will be heightened for the next three hours. If one eats the blue fish, the calming water will have no effects on them for the next 24 hours.


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''The Cave Natives'''''</span>===

The Cave Natives are an elusive and shy group of humanoid-like aquatic entities that reside in the caves of '''Level 481'''. They are generally shy of people and will go out of their way to avoid people at all costs. Despite their shy nature, however, they have interacted with a few people, even if only very briefly.

The Cave Natives have humanoid-like appearances and behaviors, such as standing on two legs and walking like a regular human. They, however, have differences that classify them as their own style of entity. They have a blueish-colored skin on them and are more of an aquatic style of creature. They have fish-style elements, such as having gills, fins, scales, etc., that make it possible to breathe underwater in the calming waters. Unlike humans, they can swim down the calming waters without the effects of it affecting them at all. Their diets mainly consist of the calming fish, although the effects of the fish do not apply to them at all.

==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Groups and Organizations'''''</span>==

Despite the relatively peaceful nature of '''Level 481''', there are no permanently established bases in the level due to it being mostly encompassed in water. Despite there being no permanent bases, there have been a few established temporary research stations, mainly to research the properties of the water in '''Level 481'''.

Despite not being in the level itself, there is a group dedicated to preserving the natural beauty of '''Level 481''' and making sure that both the level and its inhabitants are safe from the outside levels and groups who want to exploit the level for their own gains. They call themselves the Ethereal Protectors, and all of them occupy the levels that lead into '''Level 481''' and make sure no one enters the level itself without their permission. If a group or person manages to get their permission, a member of the Ethereal Protectors will travel with them to make sure they don't harm either the level itself or its occupants. 

==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Entrances and Exits'''''</span>==


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Entrances'''''</span>===

In [[Level 200.8]], if one manages to find a massive wall of glowing blue water and walks through it, they will end up here.

In [[Level 907]], if one goes to section 4 and finds an out-of-place glowing water and drinks a cup of it, they will fall asleep and wake up here.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Exits'''''</span>===

If one finds a blue book on the ground with the title reading "Heaven Awaits" and reads the first page, they will be brought to [[Level 37.2]]. If it is a red book however with the same title, they will instead be brought to [[Level 34]].

If one finds a series of trident symbols, they must close their eyes and think of severely disfigured buildings and landscapes. Once they do, they will be brought to [[Level 94]]. 


{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<u>'''The Diary of Paulus Garschall.'''</u>|final='''<u>I hope to them and us...they and we learn that humanity can only be what it wants to be.</u>|body=
<br>''''


{{Blurimage|file=River Ybbs.png|caption=The River Ybbs of my native Austria.|align=center}}

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Before I arrived at the caves.'''''</span>===

"There is not much I remember before falling [[Level 0|into what was my new home.]] But what I can remember, I remember well. I remember I grew up in a town near the River Ybbs. If I am remembering correctly, it was the town of Amstetten, a town of around 20000 people. Despite living there, I was never interested in the town itself. Rather, I was interested in the nature around it. I always spent a majority of my time outside near the River Ybbs, always admiring the natural beauty, the way it naturally flowed. I couldn't think of anything more beautiful than nature, and that extends to me, even now."

"I was never alone whenever I went out there into the vast swaths of Austrian nature. I always had the creatures within those swaths to keep me company. Despite being human, I never wanted to socialize with my own kind. I was never really sure why though; perhaps it was their ignorance of the natural beauty that always surrounded the homes and buildings that they built. Or perhaps it was their destructive nature towards that natural beauty. Either way, I never understood the nature of humanity despite being a human myself. What I do know is that I loved the species of nature that were not my own."

"It was perhaps that element I missed the most when I finally fell into [[Level 0|this realm.]] I was walking alongside the River Ybbs, observing it flowing. Then all of a sudden...I just fell through the ground. I was, of course, at first, terrified. I asked all the questions without even having the answers themselves until much later. Through it all, I first navigated a level filled with yellow walls, flickering lights, dirty carpet floors, etc. It took some time, but I eventually accepted the fate that perhaps nature itself assigned me, even if I didn't understand what that assignment was."

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''My experience with humanity and the lies they produce.'''''</span>===

"A few years passed when I went from my old home to my new one. I discovered quickly that the yellow walls were but a tiny percentage of the true expanse that awaited me. I soon found some humanity in these lands of vast emptiness. For the first time in my life, I was part of a group. It was a small group of around 9 people; they said that they were a nature group dedicated to preserving the natural beauty of various levels. I of course was very much interested and soon joined them and fought for their cause."
"It soon became apparent, however, that greed could be persuaded above all else. During a stay at one of the levels, we vowed to keep safe from developers who wanted to build on it. I saw one of the group members take a bribe. I attempted to notify another member of our group, but they just ignored me like it was no big deal to them. After seeing that, I wanted to do something. But I was only one man against 9 others and had to let it go. I left a note notifying them of my intentions to leave the group and what I saw. I never got a response back from any of them."

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''I arrive to the caves.'''''</span>===

"The only friends I ever had were never truly friends in the end. Their support for nature was nothing more than a publicity stunt for them. Behind those masks of environmental preservation were faces of greed. At least that is what I thought in the end. After I left, I vowed to never interact with any human being again, only having to when I need food or drinks to survive on."

"I wandered and wandered, looking for something. I was never sure what I was looking for, but it was something. And soon, I found it. After wandering for some time, I found myself in [[Level 200.8| a land of marble.]] I found this land intriguing for a while. I wished I could live there, but the lack of natural resources within that level made it nigh on impossible to do so."

"I eventually found something, however, inside that level that would lead me finally...to my final home. I was walking around the inner quarry when I spotted something out-of-place. It was a wall of water. As odd as it both sounded and looked, I was naturally curious and soon enough walked through it. I thought I would have to hold my breath at first, but oddly enough I didn't need to. After traversing through the water for around ten minutes, I ended up in a place quite like no other."

"My initial reaction to this place upon laying my eyes on it for the first time was; (What is this...heaven?). I was fascinated by this place, as I had never heard anything like it when I was traversing other levels. I have indeed heard levels with caves and even levels with water caves. But something seemed...different about this place. Every surface was a marble surface, and the water had an inviting blue to it. I decided to taste the water, and it was perhaps the best water I have ever had."

"In that water, I also soon found various fish. I grabbed what was a blue-colored fish. I had an odd sensation that I did not need to cook it and to just eat right then and there. I let my thoughts get the better of me, and I did indeed take a bite. Oddly enough, however, it seems I did not need to cook it after all. It had a rich taste and was one of the best foods I had tasted in a long time. With both the water and food, and with that fact, it seemed no one else really knew about this level...I had made my choice. This would be my home from now on."

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''The native creatures around me.'''''</span>===

"If someone had told me years ago that my home would consist of entirely marble caves with water that calms the soul, I would be very, very confused. But in essence, that describes where I live now. Out of all the things life could have given me, I would say this was perhaps the most confusing, but yet perhaps also the best thing life has given me. Perhaps this was the post life assigned me. I believe that life put me here to protect it, and I will."

"But it seems I was never alone in protecting this level. Of the few people I have chased off in this level, it seems a few more were chased off by something else. I did not really pay attention much to that detail, but once I thought about it some more, the more I realized something. I wasn't alone in these marble caves."

"And soon enough, I began seeing shadows. I at first thought that somehow, a group managed to establish themselves here. But the more I saw the shadows, the more I realized that they weren't human at all. They did have human-like features, but the shadows didn't exactly scream human to me. I pose myself a question about them, however. If they are not human but yet have human-like features, will they behave like a human?"

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''Am I a god to them?'''''</span>===

"It has been around a few months since I arrived here, and I must say, it has been the best decision I ever made. Something about these marble caves, something about these waters—they speak to me. It gives me feelings I have not felt since all the way back to the days I was walking along the River Ybbs. It is those feelings that make me who I am now. This place, my new home...I couldn't have asked for a better one."

"Soon enough, it would not only be the caves and water themselves that made it home, but it would be the creatures inhabiting it. Over the last few weeks or so, I have noticed an increase in shadows. It was odd, since there wasn't anybody to chase off. Soon enough, I came to the conclusion that those creatures were observing me. At first, I did not know what that meant. But when I came across a cave painting of myself, I theorized that I was some sort of symbol to them."


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''My encounter with one of their own.'''''</span>===

"After a few more months, I noticed more cave paintings of myself and even random fish lying on the grounds where I usually catch the fish. I wanted to interact with them, but their elusive nature meant I couldn't find where they lived. After awhile, I was starting to lose hope in ever meeting one of them. But to my surprise, one day I came across an injured female native. It was a shock to see what they actually look like. They appeared to have blue skin, brown hair, and grey eyes. They both had features of humans and fish."

"At first, she seemed scared and wanted to flee, but I noticed her leg was in pain. I couldn't really do anything, but I did comfort her as best as I could. Soon enough, after a few hours, I saw two of the natives arrive. They were scared and wouldn't even come near me and her. Recognizing their fears, however, I slowly backed up, and slowly they moved forwards towards the injured female. After they went to her, I left the vicinity. I wasn't sure exactly what happened there or if they treated my actions as friendly or hostile. Either way, it made one thing clear for me. They did not trust humans."



===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#c9f6ff; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #c9f6ff">'''''My time is coming to an end.'''''</span>===

"Some more months passed before what would be my next and final interaction with them. It was becoming apparent that my health was failing. Though the water could remove any thoughts for a bit, and the pink fish could provide temporary positive thoughts for around an hour, nothing could ever distract me from the pain my body felt in my final days."
"That's what I thought at least for a while. But...she arrived to comfort me. At first, it was hard to believe it was really her, since I know they are usually very evasive of humans. But seeing as how they painted me on the walls of the caves, I guess it was to be expected in the end; I am one they respect."

"As soon as I saw her, she had a visible look of concern on her face...And it was the first time I had actually heard any of them speak. I heard her ask, "You okay?" I was surprised but composed myself and said that I was fine. I asked her what her name was. She was nervous, but she said "Name is Lucy. Yours?" I said that my name was Paulus. It took her a second to process and say my name correctly, but she did say it correctly after a couple of tries."

"We soon had a conversation, or at least the best we could. She had learned very little English, but she put it to good use. She explained that her people had lived in these caves for as long as they could remember and that they had only recently begun encountering humans like me in the past 20 or so years."

"I eventually told everything about my life, and in exchange, she told me everything of hers. We talked for a long time, and through all of it, I came to a realization. She was more human here than anywhere else in this realm. Perhaps it was just the way I am, but I never really trusted humanity, only nature itself. Soon enough, she had to leave. I knew this would be our final interaction, so I gave her something special. It was something I had since that day I fell into this realm: a pocket watch. It was my last gift I could give to nature."

"In my final hours, however, I began to reevaluate everything I ever thought. Was humanity really that bad? Perhaps so, perhaps not. But in the end I realized both were true. In this world and [[The Frontrooms|the other one]], there were humans who were evil, but also humans that were good. Good and evil are things that can never be truly defined in one person. There are things we know about them that they don't know themselves, but there are also things about themselves we will never understand. What we perceive as evil can be perceived as good by others, and vice versa. It is with those thoughts in the end...that I realize humanity is not defined by any one word. To the world, I say this. Live by yourself but also live by what surrounds you. Look to yourself and to others, and never let one outweigh the other."

}}

